# Q1.1
class myknn_regressor():
    def __init__(self, n_neighbors = 10, mean_type = "equal_weight"):
        """mean_type can be equal_weight or remove_outliers.
                              equal_weight use the same weight for all neighbors.
                              remove_outliers remove neighbors out in [Q1 - 1.5 IQR, Q3 + 1.5IQR]."""
        self.n_neighbors= n_neighbors
        self.mean_type= mean_type
        
    def fit(self, x_train, y_train):
         ### Add your code here ###
        self.x_train = x_train
        self.y_train = y_train

    def predict(self, x_test):
        """use remove_outliers only if k>=10"""
         ### Add your code here ###
        if self.mean_type == "equal_weight" or self.n_neighbors < 10:
            distances = self.compute_distances(x_test)
            test_labels = self.predict_labels(distances)
            return test_labels
        if self.mean_type == "remove_outliers" and self.n_neighbors >= 10:
            distances = self.compute_distances(x_test)
            test_labels = self.predict_labels(distances)
            
            return test_labels
    def compute_distances(self, x_test):
        num_test = x_test.shape[0]
        num_train = self.x_train.shape[0]
        distances = np.zeros((num_test, num_train))
        for i in range(num_test):
            for j in range(num_train):
                distances[i][j] = np.sum((x_test[i]-self.x_train[j])**2)**0.5
        return distances

    def predict_labels(self, distances):
        num_test = distances.shape[0]
        y_pred = np.zeros(num_test)
        if self.mean_type == "equal_weight" or self.n_neighbors < 10:
            for i in range(num_test):
                closest_y = []
                closest_y = self.y_train[np.argsort(distances[i])[:self.n_neighbors]]
                y_pred[i] = sum(closest_y)/self.n_neighbors
            return y_pred
        if self.mean_type == "remove_outliers" and self.n_neighbors >= 10:
            for i in range(num_test):
                closest_y2 = []
                closest_y = []
                closest_y2 = self.y_train[np.argsort(distances[i])[:self.n_neighbors]]
                closest_y2 = np.sort(closest_y2)
                Q1 = np.percentile(closest_y2, 25)
                Q3 = np.percentile(closest_y2, 75)
                iqr = Q3 - Q1

                for j in range(self.n_neighbors):
                    if (closest_y2[j] <= Q3 + 1.5*iqr) and (closest_y2[j] >= Q1 - 1.5*iqr):
                        closest_y.append(closest_y2[j])
                y_pred[i] = sum(closest_y)/len(closest_y)
            return y_pred

myknn = myknn_regressor(20, "equal_weight")
myknn.fit(X_train, Y_train)
ypred = myknn.predict(X_test)

def rmse(y_pred, y_test):
    rmse_result = (np.sum((y_test-y_pred)**2)/y_pred.shape[0])**0.5
    return rmse_result

def rmse2(y_pred, y_test):
    rmse_result = (np.sum((y_test-y_pred)**2)/y_pred.shape[0])**0.5
    return rmse_result

#Q3.2
import numpy as np

class mylasso():
    def __init__(self, lamcoef = 0.1, max_iter=1000, tol=1e-6, const_regu = False):
        """lamcoef: the regularization coefficient
           max_iter: maximum number of iteration for model training
           tol: tolerance for the stopping criteria for model training
           const_regu: whether the constant term should be regularized, default to False
           """
        self.lamcoef = lamcoef
        self.max_iter = max_iter
        self.tol = tol
        self.const_regu = const_regu
        
    def fit(self, x_train, y_train, winit = "ridge", keep_traindata = True, verbose = False):
        """Fit a Lasso model
           x_train: a numpy matrix that contains training features
           y_train: a numpy matrix that contains the label
           winit: how weights are initialized, default to "ridge", ridge regression
           keep_traindata: whether the object is going to keep training data after the training process completed
           verbose: output a lot of message"""
        #keep_traindatamylassoTraining DataAttributeTraining Data
        if keep_traindata == True:
            self.x_train = x_train
            self.y_train = y_train
        self.m, self.n = x_train.shape #mn
        self.w = np.zeros(self.n)
        self.winit = winit
        self.keep_traindata = keep_traindata
        self.verbose = verbose
        
        #x_train
        col_const = np.ones((self.m, 1))
        x_intercept = np.concatenate((col_const, x_train), axis = 1)
        
        #w
        w = np.dot(np.dot(np.linalg.inv(self.lamcoef*np.identity(self.n + 1) + np.dot(x_intercept.T, x_intercept)), x_intercept.T), y_train)
        self.w0 = w[0]
        self.w = w[1:]
        
        # lw
        last_loss = 10000000000000
        min_loss = 100000000000000
        min_loss_w = self.w
        min_loss_w0 = self.w0
        for i in range(self.max_iter):
            for j in range(self.n):
                x_noj = np.delete(x_train, j, axis = 1)
                w_noj = np.delete(self.w, j, axis = 0)
                a = y_train - np.dot(x_noj,w_noj) - self.w0
                w_jstar = np.dot(y_train - np.dot(x_noj,w_noj) - self.w0, x_train[:, j]) / np.dot(x_train[:, j],x_train[:, j])
                th = (self.m * self.lamcoef) / np.dot(x_train[:, j],x_train[:, j])
                
                if self.w[j] > th:
                    self.w[j] = w_jstar - th
                elif self.w[j] < -th:
                    self.w[j] = w_jstar + th
                else:
                    self.w[j] = 0 
            if self.const_regu == True:
                if np.mean(y_train - np.dot(x_train, self.w)) - self.lamcoef > 0:
                    self.w0 = np.mean(y_train - np.dot(x_train, self.w)) - self.lamcoef
                elif np.mean(y_train - np.dot(x_train, self.w)) - self.lamcoef < 0:
                    self.w0 = np.mean(y_train - np.dot(x_train, self.w)) + self.lamcoef
                else:
                    self.w0 = 0
            else:
                self.w0 = np.mean(y_train - np.dot(x_train, self.w))
        #L
            if self.const_regu == True:
                loss = np.mean(np.square(y_train - np.dot(x_train,self.w) - self.w0))*0.5 + self.lamcoef*(abs(self.w0) + np.sum(abs(self.w)))
            else: 
                loss = np.mean(np.square(y_train - np.dot(x_train,self.w) - self.w0))*0.5+ self.lamcoef*np.sum(abs(self.w))
            if loss < min_loss:
                min_loss = loss
                min_loss_w = self.w
                min_loss_w0 = self.w0
            if abs(last_loss - loss) < self.tol:
                break
            last_loss = loss
         
        nonzero = 0
        for i in min_loss_w:
            if i != 0:
                nonzero += 1
        # ww0
        self.optimize_w = min_loss_w
        self.optimize_w0 = min_loss_w0
        self.min_loss = min_loss
        self.nonzero = nonzero
                
        


    def predict(self, x_test):
        """Make prediction using trained model"""
        ypred = np.dot(x_test, self.optimize_w) + self.optimize_w0
        return ypred
            

    np.set_printoptions(suppress=True)
mlo =mylasso(lamcoef = 0.1)

ypred = mlo.predict(X_train_sd)

training_loss = []
nonzero = []
MAW = []
training_rmse = []
test_rmse = []
np.set_printoptions(suppress=True)
lambda_list = [0.0001, 0.0005, 0.001, 0.005, 0.01, 0.05, 0.1, 0.5, 1, 2]
for i in lambda_list:
    mlo = mylasso(lamcoef = i)
    mlo.fit(X_train_sd, Y_train)
    ypred = mlo.predict(X_train_sd)
    training_loss.append(mlo.min_loss)
    nonzero.append(mlo.nonzero)
    MAW.append(np.mean(abs(mlo.optimize_w)))
    RMSE = np.sqrt(np.mean(np.square(Y_train - ypred)))
    training_rmse.append(RMSE)
    ypred = mlo.predict(X_test_sd)
    RMSE = np.sqrt(np.mean(np.square(Y_test - ypred)))
    test_rmse.append(RMSE)
import pandas as pd
dataframe = pd.DataFrame({'Training Loss':training_loss, 'Number of Non-zero Weight': nonzero,'Average Weight Size': MAW, 'Train RMSE': training_rmse, 'Test RMSE': test_rmse}, index=lambda_list)
dataframe.index = [0.0001, 0.0005, 0.001, 0.005, 0.01, 0.05, 0.1, 0.5, 1, 2]
